{
  "stem": "5371.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I did work carpenter work, not that I knew much about it, but I did work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So being there was much better, because I was every night home with my family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I also was able to provide some food for them, because at the railroad station, they were bringing in a lot of different things, you know?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were actually stealing food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whenever they unloaded potatoes or-- but mainly potatoes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we used to bag some-- take in bags some potatoes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or we used to tie our pants on the bottom and putting inside our pants some potatoes, because they don't-- they didn't allow you to do-- to take anything.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were there 'til the end of 1941.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then they decided to evacuate half of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were in that part, you know-- because actually the Jewish committee, which took care of all the transports, of course, according to the orders from the Germans, they will take first people who are not from the town, but they'll take all the oncoming people from different towns, because there were people there from different towns.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they first sent-- naturally, they gave priority to their own people, from their own town.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they shipped first the people from the other towns.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So naturally we were not from this town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were from another town, so we-- we were among the Jewish people who were shipped out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were shipped to Miedzyrzec, which is in the Lublin area, near Biala Podlaska.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a 90% Jewish town.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they put us all up in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we knew that my brother, who was in the army-- he was taken prisoner of war, and they were taken back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
